# Trivy ignore file for MLOps Platform
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/v0.28.0/docs/configuration/filtering/

# Ignore false positives and accepted risks for IaC scanning

# AWS Provider warnings that are handled by organizational policies
# AVD-AWS-0057: VPC Flow Logs - enabled via organizational CloudTrail
# AVD-AWS-0178: EBS encryption - using default KMS key is acceptable for dev

# Kubernetes manifest warnings that are intentional for ML workloads
# KSV001: Process can elevate privileges - needed for GPU workloads
# KSV003: Default capabilities not dropped - handled by PodSecurityPolicy
# KSV012: Runs as root - some ML frameworks require this
# KSV014: Root filesystem not read-only - ML models need write access
# KSV021: Low user/group ID - acceptable for internal services

# Terraform state file warnings
# Generic secrets detected - these are Terraform state references, not actual secrets